      <div class="msgContentFrame">Going to have to trounce on the concept of &quot;orb color recommends action&quot;.  There's no established evidence of this.  A few hundred synths properly cataloged would go a long way to establishing a pattern but in reality, you're best served by evaluating your outcome and using the ability that will get you to that outcome with the highest chance for success.  If you're simply aiming for completion, you probably shouldn't be using anything other than standard synthesis.  If you're aiming for quality with a synth that is a bit risky, you can build up to 60-80 progress and try to finish with bold.  If you're at serious risk of failing the synth with Standard, you can try for the &quot;Hail Mary&quot; approach with Rapid and usually wind up failing anyways.  If you're way above the ideal rank for synthesis and quality is the goal, Bold as much as you can. <br /></div>
      <div class="msgFtFrame">
        <div class="msgFtFrameFix"></div>
