      <div class="msgContentFrame">Aurelius nailed it, imho. A guy in my LS has been doing some experiments with Harmonize.  The skill says that it reduces risk, so he used it on each different color orb and these are the results he got: <br /> <br />Flashing turned to red <br />Red turned to yellow  <br />Yellow turned to white <br />White stayed the same <br /> <br />This leads me to believe that the orb colors are exactly what SE stated they are: risk factors associated with the synthesis.  All of this rapid/bold on red/yellow is just BS people started when no one had an idea what the colors meant, and since they believe it, they see patterns that aren't there. I'm guilty of it myself.  Flashing always seemed  to me to get more successes than red, but according to Harmonize flashing is the most risky, and I forced this pattern into my own head by associating Red with bad and always waiting on it; therefore, I was never able to really compare my success rate with red to flashing.  <br /> <br />Until someone actually sits down, and catalogs all of their synths and gets a good base number of attempts for each type on each color (1000+), then we can start to draw more accurate conclusions.  As for now, I am going to believe what the game creators have told me. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Oct 13th 2010 11:57am by Rysa </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Drake Wulfric - Selbina Server</div></div>
