      <div class="msgContentFrame">Being disapointed with the ammount of flames and tears going on in the main forum I mearly decided to post information I though could be useful in this forum. I do appreciate that your points of view are put forward in a polite way and am not taking it personally. <br /> <br /><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Quote:</div><div class="orig">Q. I haven't been having much success crafting items. What am I doing wrong? <br /> <br />A. The colored, glowing graphics provides players with a large hint toward a successful synthesis. When the glow is white, the synthesis is at its most stable, and the chances of success are high. When the glow takes on a color, however, the chances of success are low. Players seeking simple completion of their synthesis rather than high-quality results should attempt to use the Wait command when the indicator is colored to restore the stability of the synthesis before finishing it. <br /> <br />Q. Is there a trick to synthesizing high-quality items? <br /> <br />A. Though synthesis actions carried out while the colored circle graphic is red suffer a reduced rate of success, they often serve to increase the quality of the synthesis. In addition, the successful execution of consecutive actions also serves to increase quality. Ultimately, the higher the quality of the synthesis process, the more likely it is to yield a high-quality result. <br /></div></div> <br /> <br />This appears to be part of an enterview between FFXIVCore and SE, check <a href="HTTP://www.ffxivcore.com/topic/22893-square-enix-ffxiv-qa-synthesis/" rel="external nofollow" title="www.ffxivcore.com/topic/22893-square-enix-ffxiv-qa-synthesis/">full enterview here</a>. <br /> <br />To be honest I didn't even know about this enterview untill I mentioned in LS chat about my ideas a a LS member mentioned that SE had already mentioned something like that. As such I though it would be helpful to share the idea/information. I know that this does not show SE clearly stating the same as me but from SE it's probbaly the most in detail we will get about the influence of colours on Synthesis. <br /> <br />Once again this is only my intuitive experience after crafting for almost 20 ranks, I do not use parsers or write down results. I do not follow an experimental method so take all my ideas/assumptions with a grain of salt.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/432524.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /> <br /> <br /><a href="HTTP://hugusff14.blogspot.com/" rel="external nofollow" title="hugusff14.blogspot.com/">My FFXIV Blog</a> <br /> <br /></div></div>
